      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, I'd be happy to help! Cold fronts are formed when a mass of cold air moves into an area occupied by warmer air, causing the warm air to rise quickly. This rising warm air cools and condenses, forming clouds and precipitation. As the cold front moves, it often brings a dramatic change in weather, including thunderstorms, heavy rain, and sometimes even severe weather like tornadoes. After a cold front passes, the weather typically becomes cooler and clearer.",
